<emphasis box="[194,321,1644,1668]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="2614">Description</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[344,454,1644,1668]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="26.[159,175,992,1014]" captionTargetBox="[443,832,174,958]" captionTargetId="figure-69@26.[439,836,170,959]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIG. 26. Limatula thalassae. Sta. z387, lateral view of shell from left side. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5250781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5250781/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="2614">figures 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[475,504,1644,1668]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="26.[161,177,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[373,904,1085,1418]" captionTargetId="figure-90@26.[371,905,1084,1419]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIG. 27. Limatula thalassae. Sta. z416, internal view of the hinge of the right valve. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5250783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5250783/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="2614">27</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[525,566,1644,1668]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="42.[160,176,1431,1453]" captionTargetBox="[160,1115,170,1394]" captionTargetId="figure-83@42.[160,1115,170,1397]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIG. 46. SEM photographs of species of Limatula and Limea. (a) Limatula thalassae; (b) Limatula laminifera; (c) Limea lirata; (d) Limea sarsi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5250844" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5250844/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="2614">46a</figureCitation>
). Shell small (max. recorded height 5.3 mm), slender, height/length ratio 1:0.56, fragile, inflated, almost as wide as long, equivalve, almost equilateral, white, ornamented with 
<emphasis box="[718,743,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="2614">ca</emphasis>
38 ribs of which 16 central ribs are prominent (of these the two most central are no more prominent), lateral ribs less prominent, growth lines strongly marked and widely separate, sharp-pointed reticulations where growth lines cross ribs, ears slightly produced with relatively deep posterior auricular sinus and much smaller and shallower anterior sinus, curvature of both posterior and anterior shell margins shallow giving shell typical elongate parallel appearance, ventral margin smoothly curved; umbos prominent; dorsal margin of hinge sharp and more or less straight at very slight angle to vertical axis, hinge plate moderately strong, without teeth; ligament central and triangular. Prodissoconch 
<emphasis box="[373,398,929,953]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="2616">ca</emphasis>
420 
<emphasis box="[451,466,929,953]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="2616">M</emphasis>
m; interdissoconch 
<emphasis box="[688,713,929,953]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="2616">ca</emphasis>
0.85 mm.
</paragraph>
